Comment_contributor: iskei is sakai, sikai of Solomon Islands
la marks the digits of the second hand, changes to li before fiti; tesa = tea
relima = rua lima; ten in fact is two-five; relima, although in fact it means two fives, and not one ten, has become to all intents and purposes a singler numeral

Value: relim e lifiti, temati e lifiti
